      "[Crawling Shore, Dockside]"
    ],
    "description": [
      "To the west, at the lowest point of the holdfast, a dock of time-silvered wood stretches out over the waters of the sea, shaking each time the waves pound against its aging timbers.  Woven baskets crowd the nearby shoreline, most empty and several pulverized and rent apart.  Up on the bluff above, huts stare outward with empty, lightless windows."
    ],
